<p dir="auto" class="break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Flyxion says: encode your history as a signal Žü(w) Ōłł ŌäØŌü┐, slap a discrete Fourier transform on it, boomŌĆö<strong class="font-semibold">spectral signature F(w)</strong>. ItŌĆÖs an <em>invariant</em> of the generative process. DoesnŌĆÖt care about surface words; it sees the underlying rhythms, recurrences, and periodic bullshit that make your Markov name generator collapse into ŌĆ£ancient wisdom traditionsŌĆØ every single time. Low-amplitude noise? Broad chaotic spectrum = real generative vitality. Concentrated peaks on the same tired frequencies? Semantic attractor collapse. You just caught your LLM red-handed being a lazy hack.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words last:mb-0 max-md:leading-[155%] max-md:mb-4 max-md:last:mb-0" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">ItŌĆÖs the math equivalent of ŌĆ£I know youŌĆÖre full of shit because your vibe frequency is off.ŌĆØ</p>
