<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A second class of objections concerns the apparent lack of computational content. We therefore provide explicit constructions demonstrating how the abstract objects of the framework admit concrete realization in existing systems.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Spectral Signatures of Generative Processes}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let a sequence <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><mo>ŌĆ”</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x = (x_1, \dots, x_n)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="minner">ŌĆ”</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">n</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> be a tokenized representation of text or system output. Define an embedding map
[
\phi : \Sigma \to \mathbb{R}^d,
]
and construct the signal
[
s_k = \phi(x_k).
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The discrete Fourier transform is then given by
[
\hat{s}\omega = \sum{k=1}^n s_k e^{-2\pi i \omega k / n}.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{definition}[Spectral Signature]
The spectral signature of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span></span></span></span> is the energy distribution
[
E(\omega) = |\hat{s}_\omega|^2.
]
\end{definition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\paragraph{Operational interpretation.}
Concentration of energy in a small set of frequencies corresponds to repetitive or attractor-dominated structure. Broad-spectrum distributions correspond to higher generative variability.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\paragraph{Empirical use.}
This quantity can be computed in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>O</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>log</mi><mo>ŌüĪ</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  O(n \log n)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">O</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop">lo<span style="margin-right: 0.01389em;">g</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> time and used to:
\begin{itemize}
\item detect collapse into semantic attractors,
\item distinguish human vs. model-generated text,
\item track diversity across generations.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Constraint Evaluation as Programmatic Verification}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žē</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \omega  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žē</span></span></span></span> be an internal structure expressed as code, formal specification, or executable process. Define
[
\mathcal{C}(\omega) =
\begin{cases}
1 &amp; \text{if execution preserves invariants}, 
0 &amp; \text{otherwise}.
\end{cases}
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In practice:
\begin{itemize}
\item compilation success,
\item unit tests,
\item invariant checks,
\end{itemize}
instantiate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus the abstract constraint field corresponds directly to existing verification pipelines.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Instantiation in Programming Languages}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In a typed programming language:
\begin{itemize}
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{S}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span></span></span></span> corresponds to well-typed programs,
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> corresponds to the type checker,
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">╬Ā</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \Pi  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">╬Ā</span></span></span></span> corresponds to interface exposure (APIs),
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{R}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">R</span></span></span></span> corresponds to execution or compilation.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Ill-typed programs are rejected, demonstrating constraint necessity. Purely generative code without type or runtime checks exhibits precisely the collapse predicted in Section 1: failure or indistinguishability of behavior.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Instantiation in LLM Pipelines}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In a typical LLM workflow:
\begin{itemize}
\item prompt construction corresponds to <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">╬Ā</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \Pi  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord">╬Ā</span></span></span></span>,
\item model inference corresponds to <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{R}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">R</span></span></span></span>,
\item post-processing or evaluation corresponds to <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{V}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.08222em;">V</span></span></span></span>.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Augmented systems (tool use, retrieval, verification loops) introduce explicit constraint coupling, reducing collapse and hallucination. This directly instantiates the Collapse Constraint.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Instantiation in Distributed Systems}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In distributed computation:
\begin{itemize}
\item logs encode irreversible history,
\item consensus protocols enforce constraint consistency,
\item divergence without constraint leads to fork or failure.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This provides a concrete realization of history-dependent coherence preservation.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Scope Clarification}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">These instantiations demonstrate that the framework does not attempt to replace biological or phenomenological theories of self. Rather, it characterizes a class of systemsŌĆöcomputational, linguistic, and informationalŌĆöin which constraint preservation governs stability and distinction.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Embodied systems may be understood as a further instantiation in which constraint evaluation is implemented through physical and metabolic processes rather than symbolic verification.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Summary}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The abstract operators of the framework admit direct realization in existing systems. Spectral signatures are computable. Constraint predicates correspond to executable checks. Projection and rendering map to established pipelines. The theory therefore does not exist solely at the level of metaphor, but admits operational interpretation across multiple domains.
\end{section}</p></div></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 mb-2 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp