se-invert break-words prose-p:opacity-100 prose-strong:opacity-100 prose-li:opacity-100 prose-ul:opacity-100 prose-ol:opacity-100 prose-ul:my-1 prose-ol:my-1 prose-li:my-2 last:prose-li:mb-3 prose-li:ps-1 prose-li:ms-1 bg-surface-l1 border border-border-l1 max-w-[100%] @sm/mainview:max-w-[90%] has-[pre]:w-full px-4 rounded-br-lg"><div class="relative"><div class="relative"><div class="relative response-content-markdown markdown [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:text-current [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:text-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose):hover]:decoration-primary [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:decoration-primary/30 [&amp;_a:not(.not-prose)]:underline-offset-2 [&amp;_h2:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h3:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0 [&amp;_h4:not(.not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\section{Derived Construction: Constraint-Coupled Generative Loop}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The preceding objections correctly identify that existing componentsŌĆöspectral analysis, verification procedures, and historical loggingŌĆödo not, in isolation, constitute a novel system. We therefore construct an operator that is not reducible to any of these independently, and which follows necessarily from the Collapse Constraint and Constraint Necessity results.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Definition of the Coupled Loop}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let
[
\mathcal{G} : \Omega \to \Sigma^*
]
be a generative operator, and let
[
\mathcal{C} : \Sigma^* \times H \to {0,1}
]
be a constraint predicate dependent on accumulated history <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We define the \emph{Constraint-Coupled Generative Loop} as the iterative system:
[
x_{t+1} = \mathcal{G}(\omega_t), \quad
\omega_{t+1} =
\begin{cases}
\mathcal{U}(\omega_t, x_{t+1}) &amp; \text{if } \mathcal{C}(x_{t+1}, H_t) = 1, 
\mathcal{R}(\omega_t, x_{t+1}) &amp; \text{otherwise},
\end{cases}
]
with
[
H_{t+1} = H_t \cdot x_{t+1}.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Here:
\begin{itemize}
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{U}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">U</span></span></span></span> is a structure-preserving update operator,
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{R}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">R</span></span></span></span> is a corrective or rejection operator,
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is an append-only history.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Non-Decomposability}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This system is not equivalent to:
\begin{enumerate}
\item a generator followed by filtering, nor
\item a verifier applied post hoc, nor
\item a static optimization procedure.
\end{enumerate}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proposition}[Coupling Necessity]
There exists no decomposition of the above loop into independent operators <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{G}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7805em; vertical-align: -0.0972em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.0593em;">G</span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> such that the resulting system preserves both:
\begin{enumerate}
\item long-term distinguishability of outputs, and
\item history-consistent coherence.
\end{enumerate}
\end{proposition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proof}[Sketch]
If <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> is applied independently of history, constraint enforcement becomes memoryless, allowing re-entry into previously invalid states. If <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{G}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7805em; vertical-align: -0.0972em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.0593em;">G</span></span></span></span> is independent of constraint feedback, outputs asymptotically collapse under interpretation (Collapse Constraint). Therefore coupling through shared state <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>Žē</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\omega_t, H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žē</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> is required.
\end{proof}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Spectral Feedback Integration}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Define the spectral functional:
[
\mathcal{S}(x) = \sum_{\omega \in \Lambda} w_\omega E(\omega),
]
where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>Žē</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  E(\omega)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žē</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> is the spectral energy and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>w</mi><mi>Žē</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  w_\omega  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.02691em;">w</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0269em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žē</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> are weighting coefficients.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We refine the constraint:
[
\mathcal{C}(x, H) = 1 \iff
\begin{cases}
\text{invariants satisfied,} 
\mathcal{S}(x) \in \mathcal{D}_H,
\end{cases}
]
where <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">D</mi><mi>H</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{D}_H  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0278em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a history-dependent admissible spectral domain.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus spectral structure is not merely measured, but feeds back into admissibility.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Derived Prediction}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The coupled system yields a prediction not present in uncoupled architectures:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Coupled Distinction]
Systems implementing the constraint-coupled loop maintain distinguishable output classes under repeated generation, whereas uncoupled systems converge to a finite set of attractors.
\end{theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\paragraph{Testable consequence.}
Given two systems:
\begin{itemize}
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{A}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span></span></span></span>: pure generator (e.g., standard sampling),
\item <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{B}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.03041em;">B</span></span></span></span>: generator with constraint-coupled loop,
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">then under repeated iteration:
[
\lim_{t \to \infty} |\text{distinct semantic classes}(\mathcal{A})| &lt; |\text{distinct semantic classes}(\mathcal{B})|.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This can be evaluated empirically using clustering or spectral divergence measures.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Irreducibility Claim}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The construction shows that:
\begin{itemize}
\item spectral analysis alone is insufficient,
\item constraint verification alone is insufficient,
\item historical logging alone is insufficient.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Only their coupling produces the predicted behavior.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Interpretation}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The significance of the loop is not that its components are novel, but that their coupling is required to avoid collapse. This coupling is not standard in existing systems, which typically separate generation, evaluation, and memory.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Conclusion}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The framework therefore yields a constructive object: a history-coupled generative system with constraint feedback. Its behavior differs from uncoupled systems in a testable manner, and its structure is not reducible to the independent application of its components.
\end{section}</p></div></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 mb-2 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp