not-prose):first-child]:mt-0"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\section{Irreversible Constraint Structures and Historical Binding}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> denote a space of admissible configurations, representations, or actions. Classical formulations of dynamical or computational systems characterize evolution as a sequence of transitions
[
x_{t+1} = T(x_t),
]
or, more generally, as stochastic transitions over <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span>. In such formulations, the present state <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is sufficient to determine admissible futures, and historical information enters, if at all, only through augmentation of state.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We consider instead systems in which admissibility is not determined solely by the present configuration, but by the accumulated trajectory through <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span>. Let
[
H_t = (x_1, x_2, \dots, x_t) \in \mathcal{H} := \bigcup_{t=0}^\infty \mathcal{X}^t
]
denote the realized history. We introduce a constraint functional
[
\mathcal{C} : \mathcal{X} \times \mathcal{H} \to {0,1},
]
and define the admissible set at time <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6151em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span></span></span></span> as
[
\mathcal{A}(H_t) = { x \in \mathcal{X} \mid \mathcal{C}(x, H_t) = 1 }.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{definition}[Irreversible Binding System]
A system is said to satisfy irreversible binding if:</p>
<katex-display-wrapper><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>ŌŖå</mo><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{A}(H_{t+1}) \subseteq \mathcal{A}(H_t),</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mbin mtight">+</span><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2083em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌŖå</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mpunct">,</span></span></span></span></span></katex-display-wrapper>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">with
[
H_{t+1} = H_t \cdot x_{t+1}, \quad x_{t+1} \in \mathcal{A}(H_t),
]
and such that no admissibility violation may be retrospectively annulled; that is, there exists no operator <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žü</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \rho  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">Žü</span></span></span></span> with <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žü</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \rho(H_{t+1}) = H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">Žü</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mbin mtight">+</span><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2083em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> preserving admissibility relations.
\end{definition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This definition induces a monotone refinement of admissible regions in <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> under temporal extension. The admissible set is not merely conditioned on history; it is \emph{contracted} by it.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Constraint Surfaces and Induced Geometry}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">For each <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, the admissible set <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{A}(H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> defines a subset of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> which we interpret as a constraint surface. The sequence <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>Ōēź</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {\mathcal{A}(H_t)}_{t \geq 0}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1449em; vertical-align: -0.3949em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.4003em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mrel mtight">Ōēź</span><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3949em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> therefore defines a nested family:
[
\mathcal{X} \supseteq \mathcal{A}(H_1) \supseteq \mathcal{A}(H_2) \supseteq \cdots.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This induces a filtration
[
\mathcal{F}_0 \supseteq \mathcal{F}_1 \supseteq \cdots, \quad \mathcal{F}_t := \mathcal{A}(H_t),
]
endowing <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> with a history-indexed structure analogous to a decreasing filtration in measure-theoretic or algebraic contexts.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{definition}[Admissibility Filtration]
The admissibility filtration associated to a trajectory <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span></span></span></span> is the sequence <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>Ōēź</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{F}t){t \geq 0}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">Ōēź</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">0</span></span></span></span></span> with <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">F</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{F}_t = \mathcal{A}(H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.09931em;">F</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0993em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>.
\end{definition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This structure is not recoverable from the terminal state <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> alone; it depends on the entire filtration.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Path Dependence and Non-Markovianity}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ŽĆ</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">H</mi><mo>ŌåÆ</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \pi : \mathcal{H} \to \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">ŽĆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.00965em;">H</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌåÆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> be the projection <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ŽĆ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \pi(H_t) = x_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">ŽĆ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>. A system is Markovian if admissibility depends only on <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ŽĆ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \pi(H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">ŽĆ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>. In the present setting, admissibility depends on <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> itself.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proposition}
Irreversible binding systems are non-Markovian in the sense that there exist <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msubsup><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">ŌĆ▓</mo></msubsup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t, H'_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.9989em; vertical-align: -0.247em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -2.453em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">ŌĆ▓</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.247em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> with <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ŽĆ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ŽĆ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msubsup><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">ŌĆ▓</mo></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \pi(H_t) = \pi(H'_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">ŽĆ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0019em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">ŽĆ</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -2.453em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">ŌĆ▓</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.247em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> but
[
\mathcal{A}(H_t) \neq \mathcal{A}(H'_t).
]
\end{proposition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proof}
Since admissibility contracts under extension, distinct histories producing the same terminal state may induce distinct filtrations, and therefore distinct admissible sets.
\end{proof}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus the state of the system is properly represented not by <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> but by the equivalence class of histories under admissibility.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Compatibility and Global Coherence}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>╬║</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>├Ś</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>ŌåÆ</mo><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \kappa : \mathcal{X} \times \mathcal{X} \to [0,1]  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">╬║</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">├Ś</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌåÆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">[</span><span class="mord">0</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mclose">]</span></span></span></span> be a symmetric compatibility kernel. Define the global coherence of a history <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> as
[
\mathcal{K}(H_t) = \prod_{1 \leq i &lt; j \leq t} \kappa(x_i, x_j).
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{definition}[Compatibility-Preserving Constraint]
The constraint functional <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> is compatibility-preserving if
[
\mathcal{C}(x_{t+1}, H_t) = 1 \implies \kappa(x_{t+1}, x_i) &gt; 0 \quad \forall i \leq t.
]
\end{definition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Coherence Preservation]
If <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> is compatibility-preserving, then for all admissible extensions,
[
\mathcal{K}(H_{t+1}) = \mathcal{K}(H_t) \cdot \prod_{i=1}^t \kappa(x_{t+1}, x_i) &gt; 0.
]
\end{theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus global coherence is maintained under admissible evolution.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Contrast with Non-Binding Evolution}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Consider a system with admissibility functional <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>ŌåÆ</mo><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}_0 : \mathcal{X} \to {0,1}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0583em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌåÆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8389em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">0</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span></span></span></span></span> independent of history. Then <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{A}_0  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is constant over time, and the induced filtration is trivial:
[
\mathcal{A}_0(H_t) = \mathcal{A}_0.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Such systems admit trajectories in which pairwise incompatibilities accumulate without restriction.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Coherence Degradation in Non-Binding Systems]
Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {x_t}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be a sequence generated under history-independent admissibility. If <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>╬║</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \kappa  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">╬║</span></span></span></span> admits incompatible pairs, then
[
\lim_{t \to \infty} \mathcal{K}(H_t) = 0
]
almost surely under sufficiently rich exploration.
\end{theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proof}[Sketch]
Since incompatibilities are not excluded, the probability of selecting incompatible pairs approaches unity as <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6151em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span></span></span></span> increases, causing multiplicative decay of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{K}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.01445em;">K</span></span></span></span>.
\end{proof}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Distinguishability Under Filtration}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>H</mi><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></msup><mi>t</mi></mrow><msup><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {H^{(i)}t}{i=1}^n  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.888em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.888em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mopen mtight">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">i</span><span class="mclose mtight">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">i</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7138em;"><span style="top: -3.1124em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be a family of histories. Define distinguishability
[
\mathcal{D}t = \frac{1}{n(n-1)} \sum{i \neq j} d(H^{(i)}_t, H^{(j)}_t),
]
for a metric <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  d  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span></span></span></span> on <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{H}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.00965em;">H</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In non-binding systems, convergence to shared attractors implies
[
\lim_{t \to \infty} \mathcal{D}_t = 0.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">In binding systems, the filtration induces divergence of admissible regions across histories, and thus <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">D</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{D}_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">D</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0278em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> remains bounded away from zero under non-degenerate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Spectral Constraint Embedding}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>ŌåÆ</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi><mi>k</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{S} : \mathcal{X} \to \mathbb{R}^k  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌåÆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8491em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathbb">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8491em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.03148em;">k</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be a feature map derived from spectral or statistical structure. Define a history-dependent admissible region
[
\mathcal{D}(H_t) \subseteq \mathbb{R}^k,
]
and refine admissibility as
[
\mathcal{C}(x, H_t) = 1 \iff
\begin{cases}
x \in \mathcal{A}(H_t), 
\mathcal{S}(x) \in \mathcal{D}(H_t).
\end{cases}
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus structural and statistical constraints are jointly enforced through the filtration.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Conclusion}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The formalism defines a class of systems characterized by monotone contraction of admissible regions under irreversible history extension. Such systems are inherently non-Markovian, path-dependent, and globally constrained. These properties distinguish them from systems in which admissibility is independent of history or subject to revision. The resulting structure is not reducible to instantaneous state dynamics, but is indexed by the filtration induced by accumulated constraints.
\end{section}</p></div></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 mb-2 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp