<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> be a measurable state space and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">H</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mo>Ōŗā</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>Ōēź</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mi>t</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{H} = \bigcup_{t \ge 0} \mathcal{X}^t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.00965em;">H</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1884em; vertical-align: -0.3949em;"></span><span class="mop"><span class="mop op-symbol small-op" style="position: relative; top: 0em;">Ōŗā</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span style="top: -2.4003em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mrel mtight">Ōēź</span><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3949em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7936em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> the space of finite histories. We consider two classes of systems evolving over <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span>:</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{itemize}
\item \emph{Non-binding systems}, in which admissibility of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x_{t+1}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6389em; vertical-align: -0.2083em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mbin mtight">+</span><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2083em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> depends on a finite-dimensional state representation <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>s</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>Žā</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  s_t = \sigma(H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>,
\item \emph{Binding systems}, in which admissibility depends on the full history <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> through a constraint functional <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{C}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span></span></span></span> satisfying monotone contraction.
\end{itemize}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We formalize these notions precisely.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Non-Binding Systems}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A non-binding system is specified by a tuple <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>Žā</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{S}, \sigma, T, \mathcal{C}_0)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">T</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0583em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> where:
[
\sigma : \mathcal{H} \to \mathcal{S}, \quad T : \mathcal{S} \to \mathcal{P}(\mathcal{X}), \quad \mathcal{C}_0 : \mathcal{X} \times \mathcal{S} \to {0,1}.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Evolution proceeds via:
[
s_t = \sigma(H_t), \quad x_{t+1} \sim T(s_t), \quad \mathcal{C}0(x{t+1}, s_t) = 1.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The essential property is that admissibility factors through <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žā</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \sigma  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span></span></span></span>, which is typically finite-dimensional or otherwise compressive.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Binding Systems}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">A binding system is specified by <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{X}, \mathcal{C})  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> with
[
\mathcal{C} : \mathcal{X} \times \mathcal{H} \to {0,1},
]
such that:</p>
<katex-display-wrapper><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>ŌŖå</mo><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><mspace width="1em"></mspace><mtext>where&nbsp;</mtext><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>=</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>Ōłł</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">\mathcal{A}(H_{t+1}) \subseteq \mathcal{A}(H_t),
\quad \text{where } \mathcal{A}(H_t) := {x \in \mathcal{X} : \mathcal{C}(x, H_t)=1}.</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mbin mtight">+</span><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2083em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌŖå</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 1em;"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">where&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">Ōłł</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span></span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></katex-display-wrapper>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">No factorization through a finite summary <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žā</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \sigma(H_t)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> is assumed.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Equivalence and Simulation}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{definition}[Simulation]
A non-binding system <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>Žā</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{S}, \sigma, T, \mathcal{C}_0)  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.13889em;">T</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3011em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0583em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">0</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> simulates a binding system <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{X}, \mathcal{C})  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> if there exists an embedding <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>╬╣</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo>Ōå¬</mo><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \iota : \mathcal{X} \hookrightarrow \mathcal{S}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">╬╣</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6943em; vertical-align: -0.011em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">Ōå¬</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span></span></span></span> such that for all histories <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  H_t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>,
[
\mathcal{A}(H_t) = { x \in \mathcal{X} : \mathcal{C}_0(x, \sigma(H_t)) = 1 }.
]
\end{definition}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus simulation requires that admissibility in the binding system be recoverable from a compressed representation.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Non-Simulability Theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We now state the central result.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Non-Simulability of Binding Systems]
Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{X}, \mathcal{C})  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span> be a binding system such that there exists an infinite sequence of histories <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {H_t}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> with strictly decreasing admissible sets:
[
\mathcal{A}(H_1) \supsetneq \mathcal{A}(H_2) \supsetneq \cdots.
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Suppose further that for each <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  t  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6151em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span></span></span></span> there exists <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>Ōłł</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  x_t \in \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6891em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">Ōłł</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span> such that:
[
x_t \in \mathcal{A}(H_{t-1}) \setminus \mathcal{A}(H_t).
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Then no non-binding system with finite-dimensional state space <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{S}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span></span></span></span> can simulate <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  (\mathcal{X}, \mathcal{C})  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span><span class="mpunct">,</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.05834em;">C</span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span>.
\end{theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proof}
Assume for contradiction that such a simulation exists with <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>dim</mi><mo>ŌüĪ</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Ōł×</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \dim(\mathcal{S}) &lt; \infty  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mop">dim</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">&lt;</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord">Ōł×</span></span></span></span>. Then the mapping <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>Žā</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant="script">H</mi><mo>ŌåÆ</mo><mi mathvariant="script">S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \sigma : \mathcal{H} \to \mathcal{S}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">Žā</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">:</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.00965em;">H</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">ŌåÆ</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.075em;">S</span></span></span></span> induces only finitely many distinct states up to resolution.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Since <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {\mathcal{A}(H_t)}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> is strictly decreasing and infinite, there must exist <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal">ŌēĀ</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">ŌĆ▓</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  t \neq t'  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel"><span class="mrel"><span class="mord vbox"><span class="thinbox"><span class="rlap"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="inner"><span class="mord"><span class="mrel">ŅĆĀ</span></span></span><span class="fix"></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace nobreak"></span><span class="mrel">=</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7519em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.7519em;"><span style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">ŌĆ▓</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> such that:
[
\sigma(H_t) = \sigma(H_{t'}).
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">By simulation,
[
\mathcal{A}(H_t) = \mathcal{A}(H_{t'}).
]</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">But by assumption,
[
\mathcal{A}(H_t) \neq \mathcal{A}(H_{t'}),
]
yielding a contradiction.
\end{proof}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Extension to Approximate Simulation}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">One may consider approximate simulation where admissibility is preserved up to tolerance <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>ŽĄ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \epsilon  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">ŽĄ</span></span></span></span> under a metric <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  d  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span></span></span></span> on subsets of <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{X}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.14643em;">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{corollary}
If the sequence <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant="script">A</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {\mathcal{A}(H_t)}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal">A</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.08125em;">H</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0813em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose">)</span></span></span></span></span> has infinite metric entropy under <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  d  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span></span></span></span>, then no finite-capacity non-binding system can approximate the binding system uniformly.
\end{corollary}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Computational Implications}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The theorem establishes that binding systems require either:
\begin{enumerate}
\item unbounded memory growth, or
\item loss of fidelity in admissibility representation.
\end{enumerate}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Thus global constraint preservation is not reducible to finite-state feedback mechanisms without degradation.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Dynamical Consequences}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Define trajectories <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  {x_t}  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.5806em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> generated under binding and non-binding regimes.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Trajectory Separation]
Let <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">T</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{T}_B  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.25417em;">T</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.2542em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.05017em;">B</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant="script">T</mi><mi>N</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  \mathcal{T}_N  </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8333em; vertical-align: -0.15em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathcal" style="margin-right: 0.25417em;">T</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3283em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.2542em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.10903em;">N</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">ŌĆŗ</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> denote the sets of admissible trajectories under binding and non-binding systems, respectively. Then:
[
\mathcal{T}_B \not\subseteq \mathcal{T}_N,
]
for any non-binding system with bounded state representation.
\end{theorem}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{proof}[Sketch]
By non-simulability, there exist histories whose admissible continuations cannot be captured by any finite summary. Therefore corresponding trajectories cannot be generated by the non-binding system.
\end{proof}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Interpretation}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The result establishes that binding systems form a strictly larger class than non-binding systems under finite representation constraints. The distinction is not merely one of degree (more memory), but of structure: admissibility depends on an uncompressed history whose influence cannot be captured by any finite sufficient statistic.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\subsection{Conclusion}</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The formal distinction between binding and non-binding systems is therefore not reducible to path dependence alone. While both classes may exhibit non-Markovian behavior, only binding systems enforce a strictly decreasing admissible set indexed by full history. This induces non-simulability under finite representations and yields qualitatively distinct dynamical behavior.
\end{section}</p></div></div><section class="inline-media-container flex flex-col gap-1 clear-both"></section><section class="auth-notification flex flex-col gap-1"></section></div></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @md/mainview:block top-11 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mr-[36px] @lg/mainview:-mr-12"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-60 disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 select-none text-fg-secondary hover:text-fg-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-fg-secondary disabled:hover:bg-transparent [&amp;_svg]:hover:text-fg-primary h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" aria-label="Edit" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><path d="M18.25 5.75C16.8693 4.36929 14.6307 4.36929 13.25 5.75L10.125 8.875L5.52404 13.476C4.86236 14.1376 4.45361 15.0104 4.36889 15.9423L4 20.0001L8.0578 19.6311C8.98967 19.5464 9.86234 19.1377 10.524 18.476L18.25 10.75C19.6307 9.36929 19.6307 7.13071 18.25 5.75V5.75Z" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M12.5 7.5L16.5 11.5" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div class="action-buttons h-8 mt-0.5 mb-2 flex flex-row flex-wrap w-full justify-end print:hidden"><div class="flex items-center w-max rounded-lg text-xs end-4 -mr-2 -mt-2 opacity-100 p-0 gap-0" style="bottom: 80px;"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:cursor-not-allowed transition-colors duration-100 [&amp