<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">The theorem makes the finite-type boundary explicit. Local enforcement is not universally sufficient. It is sufficient exactly when the admissibility language factors through finitely many bounded obstructions. Outside that regime, any claim that local checking guarantees global consistency is false.</p>
