<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Intuitively, non-finite-type consistency means that no bounded local window captures the criterion of admissibility. The obstruction is intrinsically global.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" node="[object Object]" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">\begin{theorem}[Failure of Local Reduction]
